                            <comment id="12913557" author="softvision" created="Wed, 22 Sep 2010 13:50:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for &quot;StandardSecurityHandler&quot; (Trunk, Rev 999590)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917318" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 3 Oct 2010 11:29:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m afraid your patch will have some unwanted side effects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In StandardSecurityHandler.prepareDocumentForEncryption() &quot;version&quot; wil be initialized as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...&lt;br/&gt;
version = computeVersionNumber();&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
private int computeVersionNumber()&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
     if(keyLength == 40)&lt;/p&gt;
     {
         return DEFAULT_VERSION;
     }
&lt;p&gt;     return 2;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So that &quot;version&quot; will be set to 1 (DEFAULT_VERSION) if &quot;keyLength&quot; equals 40.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we have a look at the if-clause extended by your patch, it is obvious that the first condition will never be reached, because &quot;version&quot; never equals 2 if &quot;keyLength&quot; equals 40. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13791359" author="martin_w_brown" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2013 09:59:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;StandardSecurityHandler.computeRevisionNumber() refers to PDF Spec 1.6 p98. This says:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Revision&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; A number specifying which revision of the standard security handler should be used to interpret this dictionary:&lt;br/&gt;
&#8226; 2 if the document is encrypted with a V value less than 2 (see Table 3.18) and does not have any of the access permissions set (by means of the P entry, below) that are designated &#8220;Revision 3 or greater&#8221; in Table 3.20&lt;br/&gt;
&#8226; 3 if the document is encrypted with a V value of 2 or 3, or has any &#8220;Revision 3 or greater&#8221; access permissions set&lt;br/&gt;
&#8226; 4 if the document is encrypted with a V value of 4&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, the current code in computeRevisionNumber() is looking at the first test where V == 2 rather than V &amp;lt; 2. Following the spec, the method should look like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; computeRevisionNumber()
    {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;(version &amp;lt; 2
            &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !policy.getPermissions().canFillInForm()
            &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !policy.getPermissions().canExtractForAccessibility()
            &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !policy.getPermissions().canPrintDegraded() )
        {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; 2;
        }
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; 3;
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13812344" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 3 Nov 2013 11:54:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed the calculation of the revision number in revision 1538341 based on Martins proposal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the contribution!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
